posts.cooked: I need some help, I don’t know what this error means: ‘’‘[CANSpark Max] IDs: 9, 10, recieved parameter invalid error parameter id 113’‘’

link_counts.title: [CAN SPARK] IDs: 1,4, Received parameter invalid error parameter id 113

posts.name: Amalan Iyengar
posts.cooked:
Hi Ryan,

ID 113 is the velocity conversion factor rate - so my best guess is you’re feeding in 0 to that function call. This could be happening if you have a line like sparkMax.setVelocityConversionFactor(1/60) - where in Java this will evaluate to 0 because it will treat 1/60 as integer division - try changing this to 1.0/60.0

If this isn’t the issue, posting your code would be helpful so we can be of more use.

posts.name: Ryan zheng
posts.cooked: here’s my code, I checked that it was doing double division but it still shows the error.

posts.cooked: @akiyengar is mostly correct.  It’s not an integer division issue, it’s a divide by zero issue.  Check your constants. You currently have gearRatio defined as 0
